sentences: Girardo Cavallazzi or Cavallazzo (Occitan: Girard or Girart Cavalaz; fl. 1225–1247) was an Italian troubadour from Lombardy.
Indeed, a Girardo Cavallazzi is recorded in Novarese documents beginning in 1225.
He was console del comune in 1227 and 1230 and console di giustizia in 1247.
